start application:

Research analytics only:
- public-data anomaly monitoring and explanation
- no trading, execution, wallet, or account actions
- outputs are suspicious-activity research signals, not legal determinations

Prerequisite (avoids ModuleNotFoundError: use the venv, not system python3):
source .venv/bin/activate
# If .venv is missing: python3 -m venv .venv && .venv/bin/pip install -r server/requirements.txt
#
# .env.local: set DATABASE_URL for Neon. If the URL contains &, wrap the whole value in
# single quotes or bash will background the rest and DATABASE_URL stays unset.

========================
LOCAL DEVELOPMENT STARTUP
========================

# terminal 1 (local proxy)
source .venv/bin/activate
source scripts/use_env.sh local
cd server && python -m uvicorn main:app --reload

# terminal 2a — one-shot jobs (same terminal, order as written)
# cross_asset_predictions: batch backfill for high-score assessments (needs OLLAMA_API_KEY).
# insider_detection already inserts cross-asset rows when each assessment is persisted; this
# module matches the GitHub Actions / Render cron job for anything that was missed.
source .venv/bin/activate
source scripts/use_env.sh local
python -m model.event_cache
python -m model.cross_asset_predictions --min-score 70 --limit 500

# terminal 2b — long-running (separate terminal; blocks until Ctrl+C)
#set OLLAMA_API_KEY / OLLAMA_MODEL in the shell
source .venv/bin/activate
source scripts/use_env.sh local
python -m model.insider_detection --all-events --max-events 500

# terminal 3 (dashboard)
# set OLLAMA_API_KEY / OLLAMA_MODEL in the shell 
source .venv/bin/activate
source scripts/use_env.sh local
streamlit run gui/app.py

#terminal 4 (news scraper)
source .venv/bin/activate
source scripts/use_env.sh local
python -m news_scraper.main --loop --interval-seconds 300

