========================
NEWS SCRAPER SCHEDULING
========================

Paths (must match what insider_detection uses: --news-path or NEWS_EVENTS_PATH):
- Default files: news_scraper/data/news_events.jsonl + .metadata.json
- Override: export NEWS_EVENTS_PATH=... and NEWS_EVENTS_METADATA_PATH=...

--- Local ---

Option A — long-running loop (extra terminal; good while developing):
  source .venv/bin/activate
  source scripts/use_env.sh local   # or remote
  pip install -r news_scraper/requirements.txt   # once
  python -m news_scraper.main --loop --interval-seconds 300

Option B — cron / systemd timer (one shot per run; append-only JSONL):
  */15 * * * * cd /path/to/polymarket_whaletracker && .venv/bin/python -m news_scraper.main
  (set cwd and use full path to venv python; load env if needed)

--- Remote ---

Option A — GitHub Actions (free-tier friendly; see DEPLOYMENT_RENDER.md):
  Workflow: .github/workflows/news-scrape.yml
  Schedule: every 10 minutes (cron: */10 * * * *)
  Writes to /tmp on the runner (ephemeral). Set secret X_BEARER_TOKEN only if you enable X in news_scraper/config.py.
  Manual run: Actions → "News Scrape Schedule" → Run workflow.

Option B — Render paid worker (render.yaml service whaletracker-pipeline):
  scripts/render_start_pipeline_worker.sh runs news loop + insider_detection on disk /var/news-data/.

Notes:
- specific-events detector defaults: min_abs=0.01, min_rel=0.02
- --all-events detector defaults: min_abs=0.015, min_rel=0.03
- replay frozen trigger payloads: python -m model.replay_evaluation --input path/to/triggers.jsonl